						<summary>

						<p>A stone pillar set up in front of the Āñjanēyasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1457 (current) Jaya, Vaiśākha śu. 10, Thursday,</hi> corresponding to 15348 A.D., April 23.</p>						

						<p>Records the establishment of a pillar <hi rend="italic">(Diva-kambhamu)</hi> at the temple of Hanumanta by Abuḷa-Tirumalayyagāru son of Annaṁgāru of Bhōjanapalli Kadamūru.</p>						

						</summary>
